The paper proposes a method for constructing compressed sensing matrices, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The method involves constructing a bipartite graph, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the phase transitions of the binary matrix associated with the bipartite graph, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the paper compares the performance of the proposed method to Gaussian random matrices, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
